---
// src/pages/privacy.astro
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const lastUpdated = "July 6, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How PatreonTV handles your data. Short version: it doesn't."
>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--text-dim);">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>
    PatreonTV is a native Apple TV app that talks directly to Patreon.
    Apart from a tiny pairing service used once at sign-in (described
    below), it has no backend. It does not send your data to us. It does
    not collect analytics on what you watch.
  </p>

  <h2>What data PatreonTV touches</h2>

  <h3>Your Patreon session</h3>
  <p>
    To sign in, your Apple TV shows a pairing code and you sign in to
    Patreon on your phone or computer. The session cookie Patreon issues
    passes through our pairing service exactly once: it is encrypted at
    rest, kept for at most ten minutes, and deleted the moment your
    Apple TV picks it up. After that it lives only in the tvOS Keychain
    on your Apple TV and never leaves your device except when the app
    calls the Patreon API on your behalf. We keep no copy and cannot
    access your account afterwards.
  </p>

  <h3>Data fetched from Patreon</h3>
  <p>
    While you use the app, PatreonTV requests posts, creator information,
    memberships, and media URLs from patreon.com. This data is displayed on
    your Apple TV and held only in memory or in an on-device cache for
    performance. It is not shared with any third party.
  </p>

  <h3>Playback progress</h3>
  <p>
    Playback position for videos you watch is stored on-device using tvOS
    <code>UserDefaults</code>. This powers the "Continue Watching" shelf
    and never leaves your Apple TV.
  </p>

  <h3>Media playback</h3>
  <p>
    Patreon-hosted video is streamed from Patreon's video hosting provider
    (currently Mux). Playback URLs are signed by Patreon and delivered
    directly to your Apple TV; PatreonTV does not proxy or intercept the
    stream. Mux may collect standard streaming diagnostics as described in
    <a href="https://www.mux.com/privacy" rel="noopener">Mux's privacy policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h3>External embeds</h3>
  <p>
    Posts containing YouTube or Vimeo embeds link out to those services.
    When you open one of those posts, PatreonTV does not stream the
    content itself; if you choose to watch, the relevant third-party app
    is opened. Their own privacy policies apply once you leave PatreonTV.
  </p>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      We do not retain your data on any server. The pairing service holds
      your encrypted session cookie for minutes at most, then deletes it.
    </li>
    <li>We do not track which posts you view, watch, or interact with.</li>
    <li>We do not use analytics SDKs, advertising SDKs, or tracking pixels.</li>
    <li>
      We do not sell, share, or rent your data — because we don't have your
      data.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Crash reports</h2>
  <p>
    If PatreonTV crashes and you have opted in to sharing diagnostic data
    with Apple, Apple may deliver an anonymized crash report to us via
    App Store Connect. These reports contain no personal information and
    no Patreon session data.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    PatreonTV is not directed at children under 13. NSFW-marked Patreon
    campaigns are filtered from the app.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    If this policy changes, the "Last updated" date at the top will change
    and — for meaningful changes — we'll surface a notice in the app.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about privacy? Reach us at
    <a href="/support">support</a>.
  </p>
</Base>
